*\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering a potential issue with the test coverage for MethodPair because it might be reported under the wrong file. There’s no other file to cover it, though. I’m pondering if I could name the test class to encompass both cases, but it feels confusing. A second dedicated MethodPair test could be an option, yet the user mentioned sticking to the active class. I’m trying to follow the guidance to keep coverage organized by class.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Implemented focused coverage for `io.grpc.auth.GoogleAuthLibraryCallCredentials$JwtHelper`.\\n\\nChanges:\\n- Added dedicated test:\\n  - `tests/src/io.grpc/grpc-auth/1.68.0/src/test/java/io_grpc/grpc_auth/GoogleAuthLibraryCallCredentialsInnerJwtHelperTest.java`\\n- Removed placeholder scaffold test:\\n  - `Grpc_authTest.java`\\n- Updated test dependency setup in:\\n  - `tests/src/io.grpc/grpc-auth/1.68.0/build.gradle`\\n  - Adds `google-auth-library-oauth2-http` using the `google-auth-library-credentials` version resolved from `grpc-auth`.\\n- Added reachability metadata needed for the JWT conversion reflection path:\\n  - `metadata/io.grpc/grpc-auth/1.68.0/reachability-metadata.json`\\n\\nThe new test exercises the public `MoreCallCredentials.from(ServiceAccountCredentials)` path with an unscoped service account, then applies request metadata and verifies a JWT bearer authorization header is produced. This reaches the remaining `JwtHelper` reflection call sites.\\n\\nTests were not run, per instruction.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_07c319aa788287460169f88c1a8c0c819ea0e84940a6b88aaf\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1040, \"output\": 1262, \"cacheRead\": 40448, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 42750, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 177789645